Acceptance Criteria - Trench to be fully laid with Bidim 34 Geotextile where groundwater is likely to be encountered (only where determined by Engineer).

Acceptance Criteria - Pipes to be placed as shown on the drawings. No laying to occur until bedding lines and levels and compaction requirements have been satisfied.
Acceptance Criteria - Once the pipe is joined and laid to the lines and levels shown on the Drawings, the Engineer must perform an inspection.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Cl.21.4.6
2.7 - Pipe Backfill - Side and Overlay Zones

Acceptance Criteria - Side and Overlay Zone backfill shall be placed in maximum lifts of 150mm and compacted to the approved standard. Backfilling shall proceed as rapidly as construction and testing of work allows. The placed backfill material shall conform with the material and compaction properties of General Fill – Side and Overlay listed in Appendix B of Engeny Water Management Technical Specification.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Appendix B. IFC Design Drawings

Acceptance Criteria - Ø100 VicRoads Class 1000 subsurface drain to be contrained within 300 x 300mm granular filter material fully wrapped in Bidim A34 Geotextile installed on road side only of trench.
Acceptance Criteria - No repairs shall be undertaken without the superintendents approval of the repair materials and procedures All repair procedures undertaken in accordance with Cl 701.25
3.1 - Compaction testing of bedding material (Concrete pipe bedding and haunch material).

Acceptance Criteria - Bedding, haunch and overlay material shall be 5-7mm "A Grade" crushed rock compacted to >95% Dry Density Ratio (RD) and 70% Density Index (ID). Compaction frequency shall be 1 test per 2 layers per 40 linear metres. PSD & Atterberg 1 test per 100m3.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Appendix B. MW 7251/08/419
3.2 - Compaction testing of bedding material (Poly pipe bedding and haunch material).

Acceptance Criteria - Bedding and embedment material shall be 5-7mm crushed rock compacted to >95% Dry Density Ratio (RD) and 70% Density Index (ID). Compaction frequency shall be 1 test per 2 layers per 40 linear metres. PSD & Atterberg 1 test per 100m3.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Appendix B.
3.3 - Compaction testing of backfill material (Pipe top backfill material - Site Won).

Acceptance Criteria - Backfill material that is site won and classified as "General Fill" shall be compacted to >98% standard MDD. Compaction frequency shall be 1 test per 2 layers per 40 linear metres. OMC -2% to OMC +2%. PSD & Atterberg 1 test per 100m3.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Appendix B.
3.4 - Compaction testing of backfill material (Pipe top backfill material - Trafficable Areas).

Acceptance Criteria - Backfill material shall be 20mm FCR CL3 compacted to >98% standard MDD. Compaction frequency shall be 1 test per 2 layers per 40 linear metres. OMC -2% to OMC +2%. PSD & Atterberg 1 test per 100m3.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Appendix B. DTP 812
Acceptance Criteria - CCTV inspection of all constructed pipelines for review and approval prior to Practical Completion of the Works.
Reference Documents - Engeny Water Management Specification Cl.21.4.8

ITC - Pre Pour Inspection - Cast-In-Place Concrete

1 - Has the approved mix design for each strength concrete grade been submitted to engineer for review and approval including details of concrete supplier, oncrete grade, target slump and types and proposetions by mass of aggregage, sand, etc.?
2 - Is the ambient temperature for concrete placement between 10 and 40 degrees Celsius and no forecast rain or excessive wind/heat?
3 - Check formwork temperature not to exceed 32ºC – use cold water spraying or protection to maintain the temperature.
4 - Is bracing adequate, with tight joints and no gaps?
5 - Is the installed formwork in accordance to the horizontal/vertical dimensional requirements?
6 - Is formwork free of cracks, rubbish and defects?
7 - Has mould oil/release agent being applied to the formwork?
8 - Is there any mould oil/release agent on the reinforcement? If so this needs to be removed from the reinforcement prior to the concrete pour.
9 - Are all external edges formed with a continuous 20 x 20mm chamfer and internal edges with a continuous 20 x 20mm fillet?
10 - Is the reinforcement free from excessive corrosion material, oil, dust and soil?
11 - Is the spacing between reinforcement correct?
12 - Is the concrete cover as per specification?
13 - Are all tie wires in place and correctly tied?
14 - Are there adequate spacers/chairs at regular intervals?
15 - Has the correct number of bars being used in the reinforcement?
16 - Are all the bars of the correct size?
17 - Is the bar diameter the correct size?
18 - Are the starter bars in the correct position?
19 - Are the starter bars and splices the correct size and number?
20 - Is there adequate lap length between bars as per design drawings?
21 - Is there a correct amount of spacing between horizontal and vertical bars?
22 - Are construction joint free of laitance and scabbled where pour is against existing concrete?
23 - Are construction joints straight and regular and in accordance with the drawings?
24 - Has the construction joint/s being moistened prior to concrete pour?
25 - Has the waterstop/s being installed as per design and drawings?
26 - If waterstops have been welded ensure the weld is continuous and not poorly formed.
Is site access adequate to the works?
Is the pour site clean and free from all debris?
Are there adequate vibrators available for the pour?
Is there suitable methods available for curing post pour? (e.g. wet hessian)
Have all block outs/penetrations being installed in accordance to the design drawings?
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - Mix design to be selected based on pavement material investigation. Binder application rates to be confirmed with client prior to start.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - The surface level of the area to be stabilised shall be confirmed to be within level tolerances prior to commencement of stabilisation. Unless otherwise specified, +15/-25mm.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - Quicklime & Hydrated Lime to meet requirements of AS1672. Cement supply to comply with AS 3972. ALI shown on delivery dockets.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - Binder shall be spread at the specified rate. In passes not exceeding 15kg/m2. No traffic to be allowed after spreading other than construction traffic. Matt test & load cell outputs recorded for QA purposes.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - If quicklime is used it shall be slaked with sufficient water to allow full slaking to take place prior to mixing. Full slaking will be deemed to have been achieved when all quicklime that has been spread has changed from a cream coloured granulate to a fine white powder and there is a cessation of rising vapours.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - Mixing shall commence as soon as practical after spreading of the cementitious binder. Water to be added as required to achieve and maintain close to optimum moisture content. Mixing depth to be physically checked.
INSPECTION / TEST METHOD - Visual/ QA report
RECORD OF CONFORMITY - Visual/ QA report
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA - Compaction of the stabilised layer shall commence immediately after mixing.
